						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara Vīra-Nañjaṇa-uḍaiyār: Piravava (Prabhava), Chittirai, 1 = 1570 A.D. ? March 28 (Sunday). The cyclic year falls in Śaka 1429.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged at the end. It records that a certain Maḍukkāḍu in Vāyiṛaikkā-nāḍu was in ruins for a long time and that six merchants (names specified) belonging to the group of Ādicheṭṭis of Śrīnāthapaṭṭaṇam of the king, arranged to recolonise the place to make it into a Nānādēśippaṭṭaṇam as well as an Añjiṉāṉ-pugal-iḍam. It also mentions Irājarājapurachchāvaḍi, Eḻukarai-nāḍu, a temple and Śuvarmaḍi.</p>						

						</summary>
